		<bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
			<head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
			<p>Kenneth A.R. Kennedy was a physical anthropologist who specilized in forensic
				anthropology and human skeletal biology in South Asia. He studied at the University
				of California, Berkeley and was Professor of Ecology and Evolutionary Biology,
				Anthropology, and Asian Studies at Cornell University.</p>
		</bioghist>
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
			<head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
			<p>Collection consists of Dr. Kennedy's research and teaching materials.</p>
		</scopecontent>
